One person has died and four others were injured in a road accident involving a matatu and private car at Ekule on the Narok-Maai Mahiu road. A police officer at the scene said the private saloon car heading to Narok was negotiating a sharp bend when it veered out of its lane and collided with a Nairobi-bound Transline minivan from Kisii.The victim who died was a passenger in the saloon car. email print email print Job boycott should be suspended to allow room for talks this week, judge rules. 32 million chickens in Kenya at risk of contracting the avian flu, Agriculture minister says.